---
description: Performance habits for Next.js and API routes
alwaysApply: true
---

# Backend / API

- Paginate list endpoints; avoid loading full tables.
- Use `Promise.all` for independent async work when it simplifies latency.
- Avoid unnecessary `force-dynamic` on routes that could be static or cached — follow existing patterns in the file.

# Frontend

- Lazy-load heavy client-only sections where it already matches project style.
- Minimize payload size: request only fields the UI needs.

# Monitoring mindset

- Prefer clear, bounded error responses over silent failures.
